    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "SYSTEM TIMETABLE, SEPTEMBER 11, 1961\nUNITED\nTHE EXTRA CARE AIRLINE\n... FLIES JETS COAST TO\nCOAST AND TO HAWAII",
      "SEATTLE/TACOMA\nSTUNANC\nPORTLAND\nEUGENE\nMINNEAPOLIS /ST. PAUL\nBESTO\nMOLINE ROCK\nAND /DAVENPORI DAYTO\nSALT LAKE CITY\nCOMIN\nNEWARK\nIN BETHLEHEM, EASTON\nALTIMORE\n/ASHINGTON\nPERE NE\nSA RANGIOU\nBRIARS\nCRAMENTO\nGRAND JUNCTIO\nFRESNO.\nNSON CITY KINGSPOR\nGREENSBORO\nALEIGH DUKTA\nSANTA BARORKA\nSAN DIEGO\nUnited flights are timed to the stars by the Elgin National Watch Company.\nWEST PALM BEACH\nFORT LAUDERDALE\nALL JETS ARE FAST\nand United, with the world's largest\njet fleet, flies jets to more U.S. cities\nthan any other airline."
